            <title>[LU-13933] Clean up quoting in various shell scripts.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13933</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running the sanity test (and possibly others) we get a message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;awk: cmd. line:1: warning: regexp escape sequence `\ &apos; is not a known regexp operator&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;This happens when a space is being escaped by a back-slash which isn&apos;t required.&#160; There are various places in various shell scripts where quoting is incorrect and/or clumsy.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
